Q: How to interrupt Flux after 3 errors A: <p>You need to track errors across the Flux and signal termination when the threshold is reached.</p>
<pre class="lang-java prettyprint-override"><code>public Flux&lt;HttpHeadersExt&gt; getHeadersListByEndPathsLimited(List&lt;String&gt; endPaths, int maxErrors) {
    AtomicInteger errorCount = new AtomicInteger(0);
    Sinks.One&lt;Object&gt; stopSignal = Sinks.one();

    return Flux.fromIterable(endPaths)
            .filter(n -&gt; !n.isEmpty())
            .flatMap(endPath -&gt; getHeadersByEndPath(endPath)
                    .onErrorResume(error -&gt; {
                        if (errorCount.incrementAndGet() &gt;= maxErrors) {
                            stopSignal.tryEmitValue(&quot;stop&quot;);
                        }
                        log.warn(&quot;Error for path {}: {}&quot;, endPath, error.getMessage());
                        return Mono.empty(); // Skip failed paths
                    }), 
                    4) // concurrency limit to control parallel requests
            .takeUntilOther(stopSignal.asMono());
}

public Mono&lt;HttpHeadersExt&gt; getHeadersByEndPath(String endPath) {
    return this.webClient.head()
            .uri(&quot;/{endPath}&quot;, endPath)
            .exchangeToMono(response -&gt; {
                if (response.statusCode().isError()) {
                    String description = getResponseDescription(response);
                    return Mono.error(new PathUnavailableException(description));
                }
                return response.toEntity(String.class)
                        .map(it -&gt; new HttpHeadersExt(it.getHeaders(), endPath));
            });
}
</code></pre>

Q: Delphi doesn&#39;t accept default sizes for TCustomControl A: <p>OK, I found an alternative way that does work (posting for others who may face the same problem):</p>
<pre><code>constructor TMyComponent.Create(AOwner: TComponent);
begin
  inherited Create(AOwner);
  if csDesigning in ComponentState then
  begin
    Width  := 200;
    Height := 25;
  end;
end;

</code></pre>

Q: Get selected value in datalist using jQuery A: <p>You just give a id to datalist. And in script, you can get the value like velow:</p>
<pre><code>var ddl = $('[name=&quot;TypeList&quot;]').val();
</code></pre>

